Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The World Rugby Council will on Wednesday announce who will host the 2023 Rugby World Cup.  The announcement will take place in London 200 years after the invention of the game of rugby by William Webb Ellis. Two weeks ago, SA’s bid in London was named as the “clear leader” and “unanimous” choice by the Rugby World Cup board to host the tournament whilst contenders France and Ireland were rated second and third respectively. eNCA